<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lacquey1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lacquey</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Lackey,</orth> subst. an attending servant, a footboy: <bibl n="shak. luc 967" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 967</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.314" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 314</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.323" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 323</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.121" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.289" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 289</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 33</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>base l. peasants,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.317" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 317</bibl></cit>.
